Throughout all of human history, there have been wars that often deeply affect the groups of people involved.  From the veterans soldiers who fight in them to the efforts of Davis citizens to support or work to end the wars, no matter your personal perspective on war, it is clear that the community of Davis have been and continue to be affected greatly by the tragic events of war throughout the history of the town.

  World War I
  World War II shut down UC Davis and resulted in not only Japanese internment, but a city resolution to banish all people of Japanese descent.
